UI/UX & Motion Design DocumentProject Name: "A Message Someone Left For You"Design Philosophy: Maximum cozy immersion followed by a brutalist, zero-transition visual shock.1. Global Visual VariablesColor PaletteThe color progression is designed to physically relax the user's eyes, making the harsh meme transition physically jarring.CSS VariableHex CodeUsagePhase--bg-pastel-pink#FFD1DCPrimary background, soft glowWholesome--bg-lavender#E6E6FASecondary background, gradientsWholesome--text-warm-white#FFF5EEStar text, overlay textWholesome--accent-soft-blue#AEC6CFStar glow, subtle highlightsWholesome--envelope-red#D9534FWax seal, heart particlesWholesome--bg-void-black#0D0D0DInstant background swap on dropMeme Twist--text-meme-white#FFFFFFPrimary meme textMeme Twist--accent-error-red#FF0000Flashing UI elements, harsh alertsMeme TwistTypographyFont loading must be prioritized to prevent layout shifts.Wholesome Font: Caveat or Dancing Script (Google Fonts). Used for the letter, the star messages, and the initial landing page. Sizes should be large and legible (e.g., 1.5rem to 2rem).Meme Font: Impact, Oswald (Extra Bold), or system default Arial Black. All text in this phase is strictly uppercase, tight line-height, with a harsh black text-shadow to mimic classic meme templates.2. Component Specifications (Mobile-First)All screens should utilize 100dvh to ensure the UI doesn't jump when mobile browser address bars appear or disappear.Phase 1: The Envelope & LetterLayout: Flexbox, align-items: center, justify-content: center.The Envelope: An SVG or WebP graphic taking up ~60% of the mobile viewport width. It needs a subtle, continuous CSS transform: translateY hovering effect (a 3-second cycle).The Letter Folds: Hidden by default (opacity: 0, height: 0). When clicked, they transition to opacity: 1 and their full height using a smooth ease-in-out curve over 600ms.Phase 2: The Jar of StarsLayout: The jar sits at the bottom center of the screen. The top 70% of the screen is empty space for the stars to float into.The Stars: Small, glowing circular divs or SVGs.Message Bubbles: When a star is clicked, it expands into a soft-edged, frosted-glass (backdrop-filter: blur(5px)) container holding the cursive text.Phase 3: The Loading Screen & TwistLoading Bar: A sleek, rounded progress bar. It should intentionally stall at 99% for a full 1.5 seconds to maximize user tension.The Reveal UI: Absolute positioning. Huge text centered on the screen. Elements should overlap slightly to feel chaotic and unpolished.3. Motion & Animation MatrixThe pacing of animations dictates the emotional response.The Wholesome Animations (Easing: cubic-bezier(0.4, 0, 0.2, 1))@keyframes float: A slow, continuous bobbing motion for the envelope and stars.Values: translateY(0px) to translateY(-10px) back to 0px.@keyframes star-release: When the jar is clicked, the star moves on a curved Bezier path upwards and scales up by 20%.@keyframes fade-in-slow: Used for the background color transition from pink to the night sky (duration: 2s).The Meme Animations (Easing: linear or steps())@keyframes violently-shake: Triggers the exact millisecond the audio drops.Values: Rapid micro-translations. translate(2px, 1px) rotate(0deg) to translate(-1px, -2px) rotate(-1deg) at 100ms intervals.@keyframes pop-in-harsh: No fade. Elements go from display: none to display: block with a transform: scale(1.2) that snaps back to scale(1.0) in 50ms.4. Sound & Interaction SynchronizationAudio must be preloaded. The browser will allow audio playback after the very first click on the envelope.User ActionVisual ResponseAudio TriggerClick EnvelopeEnvelope opens, letter slides uppiano_bgm.mp3 (loops), paper_rustle.mp3Click Letter FoldText reveals smoothlysoft_page_turn.mp3Click "Continue"Pink fades to night sky, Jar appearsnight_ambience.mp3 (loops)Click JarStar floats up, message appearssparkle_chime.mp3Loading hits 100%Instant cut to Black. Screen shakes.record_scratch.mp3 (cuts all BGM)Auto-sequence 